claim.claim-text:
4. A method of preparing a fluoride characterised in that it comprises, carried out in the absence of moisture and oxygen, advantageously under reduced pressure, the successive steps below: 
preparing a molten mass of a fluoride of an alkali metal or alkaline-earth metal; 
allowing said molten mass to flow through at least one orifice emerging into a space; a consequent difference in temperature being maintained between the temperature of said molten mass and that of said space into which said molten mass is introduced, so that at the outlet of said orifice(s), said molten mass becomes divided into droplets; 
allowing the said droplets to fall along the vertical axis of said space, causing their progressive solidification; 
recovering the totally solidified droplets in the form of beads.
